The paper proposes a method for learning directed generative models with many latent variables, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper focuses on preserving the dependencies among the latent variables, which suggests a focus on representation learning. The proposed method is evaluated on benchmark datasets, which suggests a focus on empirical evaluation. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
